Fourth Session of 11th SPA Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The fourth session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK was held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Tuesday.
 Deputies to the SPA were present there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions and those in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and the press attended the session as observers.
 The platform was taken by Kim Yong Nam, Jo Myong Rok, Pak Pong Ju, Kim Yong Chun, Jon Pyong Ho, Ri Yong Mu, Yang Hyong Sop, Choe Yong Rim, Chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party Kim Yong Dae, Chairwoman of the Central Committee of the Chondoist Chongu Party Ryu Mi Yong and members of the SPA Presidium, and Chief Vice-Chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan Ho Jong Man.
 The chairman and vice-chairmen of the SPA took their seats. 
 Chairman Choe Thae Bok made an opening address. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Following agenda items were discussed at the session: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
1. On the review of the work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 94 (2005) and its tasks for Juche 95 (2006). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
2. On the results of the implementation of the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 94 (2005) and its state budget for Juche 95 (2006). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
3. On stepping up the development of science and technology to give strong impetus to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy to SPA Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, made a report on the first agenda item. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report on the second one was made by Deputy to SPA and Vice-Premier Ro Tu Chol.
 Speakers expressed full support and approval of the reports made on the first and second agenda items, noting that the work of the Cabinet and the results of the implementation of the state budget last year were properly reviewed and clear-cut tasks for this year were set forth so as to bring about a fresh surge in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with the might of Songun and that the state budget was shaped in such a correct manner as to effect a significant turn in the economic construction and in the improvement of the standard of the people's living.
 A decision of the DPRK SPA "On approving the report on the work of the Cabinet of the DPRK and the results of the implementation of the state budget for Juche 94 (2005)" and an ordinance of the DPRK SPA "On the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 95 (2006)" were adopted with the unanimous approval of the deputies.
 Deputy Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, made a report on the third agenda item. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers on this item stressed the need to intensify the scientific and technical revolutions as required by principles of the IT age in the new century under the banner of Songun so as to bring about a big leap forward in the development of the nation's science and technology and provide a firm scientific and technological guarantee for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A decision of the DPRK SPA "On stepping up the development of science and technology to give strong impetus to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation" was adopted with the unanimous approval of the deputies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok made a closing address.

SPA Discusses Tasks of Cabinet, State Budget and Development of Science and Technology 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The 4th session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK was held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Tuesday.
 The session discussed the agenda items "1. On the Review of the Work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 94 (2005) and Its Tasks for Juche 95 (2006)", "2. On the Results of the Implementation of the State Budget of the DPRK for Juche 94 (2005) and Its State Budget for Juche 95 (2006)" and "3. On Stepping Up the Development of Science and Technology to Give Strong Impetus to the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy to the SPA Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, in his report on the first agenda item said that it is the main task to be tackled in the economic work this year to decisively increase the agricultural production for satisfactorily solving the food problem of the people, significantly boost the coal and metal production and bring about a leap forward in updating the overall national economy and reenergizing the production with a view to fully demonstrating the might of the socialist independent national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cabinet will pay deep attention to the improvement and development of the external economic work as required by the changed circumstances and realistic demand to consolidate the export bases in all fields of national economy, systematically increase the items of exports and their production, actively explore new foreign markets and make the foreign trade diversified and multilateral, he said, adding that it will positively conduct external economic cooperation including joint venture and collaboration with overseas Korean businessmen and enterprises of different countries on the principle of introducing advanced technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy to the SPA Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, in his report on the second agenda item said that the state budgetary revenue for this year is expected to increase 7.1 percent over last year while the total state budgetary expenditure 3.5 percent over last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 15.9 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure for this year will be allocated as defence spending to bolster up the People's Army, the core of the self-defensive national defence power and the vanguard of the Songun revolution, develop the defence industry and thoroughly implement the policy of the Workers' Party of Korea for putting all the people under arms and turning the whole country into a fortress, he emphasized.
 Deputy to the SPA Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, in his report on the third agenda item underscored the need to thoroughly implement the present five-year plan for the development of science and technology as an immediate task and work out well the next-term five-year plan for the development of science and technology ending in Juche 101 (2012), the 100th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung, and make thorough-going preparations for its implementation. He also called for setting out the strategy for scientific and technological development ending in Juche 111 (2022) to put the DPRK on the position of a scientific and technological power without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important for the field of science and technology at present is to lay a firm foundation for the latest science and technology and ultra-modern industry, solve the urgent economic issues including the food and energy problems on a preferential basis and energetically speed up the updating of the key industrial domains in the direction of strengthening the Juche character of the national economy, he noted.
 He underlined the need to have bold and wide-ranging scientific and technological exchange and cooperation with other countries, actively organize joint researches with their scientific research institutions and boost the creative cooperation with overseas Korean scientists and technicians.

Report on State Budget 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol made a report on the second agenda item "On the results of the implementation of state budget of the DPRK for Juche 94 (2005) and its state budget for Juche 95 (2006)" at the fourth session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly held here Tuesday.
 The reporter said that the general march for Songun revolution was dynamically made last year to mark the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 60th anniversary of the country's liberation as grand festivals of victors under the Party's Songun revolutionary leadership and as a result great achievements were made in the production and construction and the state budget was satisfactorily implemented. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to his report, the state budgetary revenue last year was fulfilled at 100.8 percent as compared with that under plan or jump of 16.1 percent over that in the previous year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revenue coming from profits of state enterprises showed an increase of 14.2 percent over that in the previous year, that from the profits of cooperative organizations 24.3 percent, that from social insurance 5.7 percent and that from others 0.3 percent.
 The local budgetary revenue was fulfilled at 114.2 percent as compared with that under plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Energetic endeavors were made to improve economic and financial management to increase the state budgetary revenue last year. This made it possible to satisfactorily meet the financial demand from the field of national defence and various other domains of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year's state budgetary expenditure was executed at 104.4 percent as compared with that under plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year 15.9 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure was allocated for national defence to meet the requirements of the WPK's Songun policy.
 The government spent 41.3 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure for various domains of national economy last year to positively spur the socialist economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A huge allocation of fund, an increase of 32.5 percent over the previous year, was made for the agricultural field, a key front of socialist economic construction, last year, thus making it possible to concentrate all forces on agriculture and bring about a fresh turn in the agricultural production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that the state budgetary revenue and expenditure for this year have been shaped in such a way as to provide a sufficient financial guarantee for the general march for the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to him, the state budgetary revenue for this year is expected to grow 7.1 percent over last year and the revenue coming from profits of state enterprises, the major source of budgetary revenue, 7.2 percent as compared with last year.
 The total budgetary expenditure will show an increase of 3.5 percent over last year.
 The state budgetary expenditure plan was shaped in such a way as to bring about a significant turn in the socialist economic construction and in the improvement of the standard of people's living, while directing utmost efforts to increasing the defence capability of the country true to the WPK's Songun revolutionary line.
 The government will allocate 15.9 percent of the total budgetary expenditure for national defence so as to bolster up the People's Army, the core of the self-defensive national defence forces and the vanguard of the Songun revolution, develop the national defence industry and thoroughly implement the Party's policy to put all the people under arms and convert the whole country into a fortress. 
 A big portion of the state budget for this year will go to the domains of national economy to put the economy as a whole on a higher level of development as required by the new century and realize the Party's intention to help the people substantially benefit from the economic foundation the country has already laid.
 12.2 percent bigger allocation of fund than last year will be made for the agricultural field, a key front of socialist economic construction, so as to thoroughly implement the Party's policy of agricultural revolution and satisfactorily solve the people's food problem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The expenditure for power, coal and metal industries and railway transport for this year is expected to increase 9.6 percent over last year and disbursement of fund for the development of science and technology 3.1 percent for the implementation of the Party's line of attaching importance to science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 3 percent more fund than last year will be disbursed for the implementation of the social policies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state plans to expand financial source through the introduction of new social insurance payment system by enterprises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government will send a huge amount of educational aid fund and stipends for the Korean children in Japan this year, too, for the development of democratic national education of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan.
 The state will encourage provinces, cities and counties to thoroughly implement the Party's policy of local budgetary system so that they may manage economic life in the local areas on their own and increase their profits so as to contribute to the state revenue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Difficult and huge are the tasks facing us this year but we are sure to emerge victorious as there are the ever-victorious Songun revolutionary leadership of  Kim Jong Il and the single-minded unity of the army and people and the independent financial foundation, he stressed.

SPA Hears Report on Work of Cabinet in 2005 and Its Tasks for 2006 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Deputy Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, made a report on the first agenda item "On the review of the work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 94 (2005) and its tasks for Juche 95 (2006)" at the 4th session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall in Pyongyang on Tuesday.
 The Cabinet planned and conducted economic work with main stress on increasing grain production, completing major objects of construction and of reconstruction and modernization  and rejuvenating overall industrial production in reliance upon the already built economic foundation by concentrating and mobilizing all potentials of the country, while implementing up to the hilt the line of economic construction in the era of Songun under the wise leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea, the reporter said, and continued:. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year witnessed successes bigger than those achieved in previous few years in the field of socialist economic construction, thanks to the patriotic endeavors of the army and people who rose up in hearty response to the joint slogan of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK calling for glorifying the 60th anniversary of the WPK as a grand festival of victors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Productive upswing that swept all the fields of the national economy led to growth in the production of main indices, notably an 11 percent gain in power generation and a 10 percent gain in coal output. This is patent proof that the economy of the country decidedly entered upon the road of rejuvenation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fresh progress was noticed in grain production under the wise leadership of the WPK which designated the agricultural front as the main front in socialist economic construction last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 130 major objects of construction and of reconstruction and modernization were successfully completed to put fresh muscles into the nation's economic foundation.
 Great efforts were directed to scientific researches and introduction of advanced science and technology last year along the Party's line of attaching importance to science and technology. As a result, over 1,050 plan targets of scientific and technological development including major objects of the state were successfully beaten to satisfactorily solve scientific and technological problems arising in the technological reconstruction and modernization of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Progress was made in educational and cultural building last year to give fuller play to the advantages of the Party's Juche-oriented policy of education and popular policy of health care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All these successes in economic and cultural construction last year, the reporter stated, were brilliant fruits reaped by the experienced and tested political ability of the Party reliably carrying forward and bringing to accomplishment the revolutionary cause of Juche under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter outlined tasks arising in giving full scope to the advantages of Korean-style socialism in all fields of politics, military affairs, economy and culture by putting another spur to the general march for Songun revolution under the militant slogan of the Party "Let us make a new leap in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with the might of Songun!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cabinet will hold fast to the principle of giving top priority to the increase of military capabilities in all fields of socialist construction and ensure with a sense of responsibility material supplies for the development of defense industry as required by the line of economic construction in the era of Songun, upholding the Songun revolutionary leadership of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the most important task facing the Cabinet this year to effect  a decisive turn in economic development and people's living by launching an all-out offensive in all fronts of the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main task in the economic work this year is to fully solve the food problem of the people by decisively increasing agricultural production, radically bolster up coal and metal production and make a leap in rebuilding and modernizing the overall national economy and rejuvenating production, thus giving unreserved scope to the might of the socialist self-reliant national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cabinet will bring a radical turn in implementing the Party's line of attaching importance to science and technology with this SPA session as a momentum.
 This year, too, the Cabinet will put great efforts into improving services for the people and bolstering land upbuilding and city management as the householder responsible for the people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will pay deep attention to the improvement of external economic activities as required by the changed circumstances and realistic demand so as to consolidate the export bases in all domains of the national economy, steadily increase the items and production of exports, actively explore new foreign markets and make foreign trade diversified and many-sided. And it will engage itself in brisk external economic cooperation including joint venture and collaboration with overseas Korean traders and manufacturers and foreign enterprises on the principle of assimilating advanced technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will also direct sizable efforts to the accelerated building of socialist culture this year to give free rein to the advantages of socialist culture in the era of Songun.
 The tasks facing the Cabinet are vast and difficulties and ordeals are still lying in the way of its activities this year. But there is no difficulty insurmountable and no fortress unconquerable as there are the invincible Songun revolutionary leadership of the Party, the heroic people and the reliable foundation of the self-reliant national economy.

Scientific and Technological Development Discussed at SPA Session 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The Fourth Session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly was held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall here on Tuesday. 
 Deputy Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea Central Committee, made a report on its third agenda item "On Stepping Up the Development of Science and Technology to Give Strong Impetus to the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter noted that the WPK unfolded a grandiose plan for building a great prosperous powerful nation and set it as one of the three mainstays for its implementation to attach importance to science and technology as well as ideology and military affairs, adopting it as its strategic line as required by the times and the developing revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result of the successful application of this line, the science and technology of the DPRK have made steady progress without stalemate or stagnation even under the unprecedentedly difficult conditions, he pointed out, and continued:
 The dynamic drive to explore fields of ultra-modern science and technology has resulted in many scientific and technological achievements.  The IC (integrated circuit) designing technology was put on a high level, the Korean-style computer-operating system and nanotechnology-based equipment developed and the latest technology developed and introduced into the prospecting of underground resources.
 Technology has made rapid progress in various major fields, the ranks of scientists and technicians have grown stronger and the material and technological foundations have been consolidated to develop the nation's science and technology as required by the work to update the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
We are faced with the important tasks to develop ultra-modern science and technology rapidly, put the nation's science and technology on an advanced, high level in a short span of time by our own efforts in reliance on the existing foundations and potentials and provide a sure scientific and technological guarantee for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation the reporter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the present, it is important to carry through the existing five-year plan for the development of science and technology and work out well the next five-year plan ending Juche 101 (2012), the 100th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung, and make thorough preparations for its implementation. It is also necessary to map out a strategy for scientific and technological development ending Juche 111 (2022) so as to definitely put the nation on a position of a scientific and technological power.
 What is important for the scientific and technological field at present is to build up a solid foundation for the latest science and technology and ultra-modern industry, solve the urgent economic problems, including food and energy problems, on a preferential basis and step up the updating of major industrial domains in the direction of strengthening the Juche character of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the field of hardcore basic technology it is urgent to build a nationwide information network and develop programming technology rapidly and thus turn our country into a power in software development. Efforts should be channeled into building a nano material industry and producing good breeds by dint of bio-engineering.
 It is important to lay more solid foundations for the development of space technology and oceanography and direct efforts to the basic scientific researches so as to intensively solve the theoretical and methodological problems pending an urgent solution for the development of the latest science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Big efforts should be exerted to build high-tech production bases in the areas where scientific and technological forces are concentrated and the intellectuals training, research and development and production are closely inter-linked. Then this will help set up centres for gradually updating the nation's economy into the one centered on the high-tech industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Great efforts will also be directed to the development of technology in important sectors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In agricultural science, it is urgent to cultivate and introduce high-yielding strains suited to the ecological and regional conditions and double-cropping through a brisk drive to bring about a radical turn in seed improvement and solve the scientific and technological problems arising in putting the agricultural production on a scientific basis and realizing the comprehensive mechanization of agriculture.
 The field of energy technology is faced with the tasks to develop the nation's fuel and power resources in a big way, speed up the technological modernization of the existing power stations, intensify the research and development of know-how to use such renewable energies as wind power and bio-energy while widely introducing advanced energy-saving technology and put the management of energy on a scientific basis.
 Particularly big efforts should be made to industrialize the method of producing iron with locally available raw materials, build a large-scale fertilizer industry based on coal gasification, develop the technology for oil exploration and processing to pave a wide avenue for developing the chemical industry and mine and process on the basis of up-to-date technology such underground resources abundant in the country as lead, zinc, magnesite, graphite, silica and building stone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The successful fulfillment of the above-said long-term plan would help rapidly develop the nation's science and technology on a higher level and definitely put the national economy on a fresh scientific and technological basis as required by the IT age.
 It is essential to improve the content, quality and method of education in the direction of intensifying the basic education and the education in ultra-modern science and technology as required by the trend of scientific and technological development in the new century and thus produce more highly qualified scientists and technicians. 
 Scientific and technological research institutions and universities and industrial establishments should actively introduce any advanced science and technology needed for our country, master them and improve them to create science and technology of our own style. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to have bold and wide-ranging scientific and technological exchange and cooperation with other countries, actively organize joint researches with their scientific institutions and boost the creative cooperation with overseas Korean scientists and technicians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 State budgetary allocations for science and technology should be sharply increased and rationally used. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter underlined the need to create a social habit and tendency whereby everyone works hard to learn science and technology and become a scientist and a technician.

Kimilsungia Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- A Kimilsungia exhibition of the Ministry of People's Security was opened on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 Displayed in the exhibition hall were many potted Kimilsungias cultivated by people's security personnel and servicepersons of the Korean People's Security Forces with sincerity in boundless reverence for President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony took place on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by leading officials of the Ministry of People's Security, general officers of the Korean People's Security Forces and people's security personnel.
 Ju Sang Song, minister of People's Security, in an opening address stressed the need for all the people's security personnel and servicepersons of the Korean People's Security Forces to hold Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the sun of Juche forever, firmly prepare themselves to be true Songun revolutionary comrades devotedly defending leader Kim Jong Il and reliably protect the socialist country and the happiness of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants went round Kimilsungias on display.

Day of Sun Commemorated in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- A national oratorical meeting of university students took place at Kim Il Sung University on Monday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 Students of Kim Il Sung University, Kim Hyong Jik University of Education and other universities said in excited tone that President Kim Il Sung showed loving care and benevolence for the university students from the day he climbed Ryongnam Hill and chose the site for the first university in new liberated Korea to the last moments of his great life. Thanks to Kim Jong Il the glorious revolutionary history of the President is given steady continuity on this land, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants expressed firm conviction that thanks to Kim Jong Il, an illustrious commander born in Mt. Paektu, the dream and hope of the young people will always come true along with the blue sky above Korea of the sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the oratorical meeting were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the C.C., the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, officials concerned and students of universities and colleges in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A performance titled "Working class sings of the leader" was given by the art squad of workers of the C.C., the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, at the Central Workers Hall Monday on the same occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang high praises of the undying revolutionary feats Kim Il Sung performed by building the powerful socialist state, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, in Korea and providing the Korean workers and other people with an independent and creative life.

Japan's Smear Campaign against DPRK and China Debunked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson Tuesday carries a signed commentary denouncing Japan for slinging mud at the DPRK and China while making a terrific uproar over "military threat."
 Shortly ago, the Defense Institute of the Japan Defense Agency in an annual report dubbed 2006 Northeast Asia Strategy Review let loose the far-fetched allegation that the DPRK's "weapons of mass destruction", ballistic missiles and nuclear issues and China's steady increase of military capabilities remained "a factor of regional instability," adding that it was necessary to reorganize the U.S. forces in the Pacific intended for "deterrence and rapid deployment" and build a highly flexible defense system in the Japan Self-Defense Forces, the commentary notes, and goes on:
 Japan's assessment of the DPRK and China as elements harassing peace and stability in Northeast Asia is a gross distortion of reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK and China, both developing countries, have keen interests in regional peace and stability. Therefore, it is illogical to say that they go for harassing peace
 As for the issues over which Japan is kicking up a big fuss, they are, to all intents and purposes, means and measures for self-defense adopted to augment their defense potential and safeguard peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In fact, huge military forces stand in confrontation on the Korean Peninsula and the DPRK and the U.S. are still technically at war. It is entirely thanks to the DPRK's powerful self-defensive means including nuclear deterrent that peace has been preserved on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an evil habit peculiar to Japan to draw waters to its own mills at the expense of others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's claim that the stance of prompt reaction involving the accelerated modernization and beefing up of armaments should be rounded off to cope with "military threats from north Korea and China" is a third-rate sophism that can work with nobody. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's arms buildup is not aimed to counter threats but to make preparations for a war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should immediately stop hare-brained plot-breeding, pondering over the catastrophic consequences to be entailed by its policy for military hegemony.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Smashing U.S. Strategy for Preemptive Attack
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The Bush administration recently announced a "national security strategy report", which outlines its main foreign policy on national security, diplomacy, military affairs, etc. for the present. In the "report" the U.S. revealed its intention to mount a preemptive attack on the independent countries and those countries disobedient to its assertion, listing them as "outposts of tyranny". 
 Rodong Sinmun today observes in a signed article in this regard:
 This is little short of a brigandish document declaring a war as it stated that the U.S. would brand as "enemies" without exception those countries refusing to follow the American view on value and would not rule out even a war to overthrow them. 
 The U.S. strategy for preemptive attack is very dangerous as it will spark a new arms race and threaten and wreck the global peace and security, the article points out, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should not be allowed to threaten and blackmail those anti-imperialist independent countries and list them as targets of its military attack for the mere reason that they refuse to follow its policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the "report" the U.S. pulled up China over the increase of military capability in an "untransparent manner". It also threatened Russia, claiming that "democracy is retrograding" there. 
 The failure to foil the above-said strategy would not only leave the independence of sovereign states seriously violated on international arena but adversely affect the human cause of independence and peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All peoples aspiring after independence and peace should mount collective attacks on the U.S. imperialists. Defence capability should be increased to smash the U.S. strategy for preemptive attack. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists in the "report" listed the DPRK as the main target of their preemptive attack. It is made the primary target of their preemptive nuclear strike.
 However, such strategy can never work on the DPRK equipped with modern offensive and defensive means. The powerful revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK have all countermeasures to cope with any possible preemptive attack from the U.S. imperialists. 
 The army and people of the DPRK will mercilessly wipe out the U.S. imperialist aggressors if they dare provoke it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The more frantic the U.S. imperialists get in their moves for preemptive attack for aggression, the further they will stand rebuffed and isolated worldwide only to meet the fate of self-destruction.
